{"questionId":"10700","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Phosphatidylcholine is an example of a phospholipid found in lecithin.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Phosphatidylcholine may be formed from propane-1,2,3-triol, two lauric acid molecules, phosphoric acid and the choline cation.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a1648d8785126670db1ba74c7ef4877ec9bac747.png\" width=\"675\" height=\"104\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Deduce the structural formula of phosphatidylcholine.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2cd3c3a74849d86f9fbbf3c3e5a3881e68a624e5.png\" width=\"80\" height=\"177\"></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/3fa33ac131f3c0b69b85b8dee49b56e8983a7a20.png\" width=\"333\" height=\"219\"></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">phosphodiester correctly drawn&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">both ester groups correctly drawn&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept protonated phosphate.</span></em></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Accept phosphodiester in centre position.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10700","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.11a(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the structural formula of phosphatidylcholine.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.3 Lipids","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}